🌐 1️⃣ Open the Project Link

Copy and paste the project link into your web browser:
https://wokwi.com/projects/456679913777533953

Press Enter to load the project page.

🔐 2️⃣ Sign In (Optional but Recommended)

To save changes or access full features:

Click "Sign In" at the top right corner

Sign in using:

Google

GitHub

Email

🖥️ 3️⃣ View the Project

After the page loads, you will see:

🧠 ESP32 Microcontroller

🌡️ Sensors (Soil, Rain, MPU6050, etc.)

📺 OLED Display

🔔 Buzzer & LEDs

💻 Code Editor (sketch.ino)

📄 diagram.json wiring layout

▶️ 4️⃣ Start the Simulation

Click the green "Start Simulation" button at the top.

The system will begin running.

Serial Monitor will display real-time readings.

🔎 5️⃣ Interact with the Project

You can:

Adjust soil moisture value (if potentiometer used)

Trigger rain sensor

Simulate motion via MPU6050

Observe OLED updates

Watch LED status changes:

🟢 Normal

🟡 Warning

🔴 Critical

Hear buzzer during critical condition

If you modify the code:

Click "Restart Simulation" to apply changes.

💾 6️⃣ Save or Share (Optional)

To save your version:

Click "Save" (Sign-in required)

To share:

Click "Share"

Copy the generated link

Send to others for review or presentation

🎯 What You Will Observe During Simulation

Real-time environmental monitoring

Automatic threshold comparison

Alert triggering mechanism

Live OLED data updates

Serial debugging output
